{"lemma":"صَلاةٌ","slug":"صَلاةٌ","root":"ص.ل.#","root_slug":"ص-ل-_","root_link":"/words/roots/ص-ل-_","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"صَلاة","root":"صلو","pos":"N","occurrence_count":83},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":6},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n24821","n24825"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B5%D9%8E%D9%84%D8%A7%D8%A9%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of صَلَّى (ṣallā) (form II)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"prayer in general; spontaneous prayer","examples":[{"text":"وَصَلِّ عَلَيْهِمْ إِنَّ صَلَاتَكَ سَكَنٌ لَهُمْ","english":"and pray for them—surely your prayer is a source of comfort for them."},{"text":"قُلِ ٱدْعُوا ٱللَّهَ أَوِ ٱدْعُوا ٱلرَّحْمَٰنَ أَيًّا مَا تَدْعُوا فَلَهُ ٱلْأَسْمَاءُ ٱلْحُسْنَى وَلَا تَجْهَرْ بِصَلَاتِكَ وَلَا تُخَافِتْ بِهَا وَٱبْتَغِ بَيْنَ ذَٰلِكَ سَبِيلًا","english":"Say (to them, O Mohammed): Call upon (Him by) \"God\" or call upon (Him by) \"ar-Raḥmân\" (\"The Merciful One\"); whichever you call upon (Him by), (remember that) the most beautiful of names belong to Him; and be not very loud in your prayers nor be very quiet but follow a way in between."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"prayer in general; spontaneous prayer; salat, namaz, prayer","examples":[{"text":"يُؤَدِّي اَلْمُسْلِمُونَ الصَّلَاةَ خَمْسَ مَرَّاتٍ فِي الْيَوْمِ","english":"Muslims perform the prayer five times a day."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"place of worship, especially of the Jews, hence a synagogue","examples":[{"text":"وَلَوْلَا دَفْعُ ٱللهِ ٱلنَّاسَ بَعْضَهُمْ بِبَعْضٍ لَّهُدِّمَتْ صَوَامِعُ وَبِيَعٌ وَّصَلَوَاتٌ وَّمَسٰجِدُ يُذْكَرُ فِيهَا ٱسْمُ ٱللهِ كَثِيرًا","english":"And were it not that God checks some people by others there in fact would have been demolished monastic cells and churches, and synagogues and mosques wherein the name of God is oft-mentioned."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"supplication, especially the supplication (from God) of blessing and well-being (on somebody)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"supplication, especially the supplication (from God) of blessing and well-being (on somebody); blessing and well-being","tags":["broadly"],"examples":[{"text":"أُولَٰئِكَ عَلَيْهِمْ صَلَوَاتٌ مِنْ رَبِّهِمْ وَرَحْمَةٌ","english":"Those are the ones upon whom are blessing and well-being as well as mercy from their Lord."}]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Normalized spelling of earlier صَلَوٰة (ṣalāh), from Classical Syriac ܨܠܘܬ (ṣəlōṯ), whence the denominal root ص ل و (ṣ l w). It is also thought to be derived from the root و ص ل (w ṣ l). Compare Ugaritic 𐎕𐎍𐎚 (ṣlt). Compare Biblical Hebrew צֶלָה (ṣélā)."},"ipa":["/sˤa.laːh/","/sˤə.ɫaːt/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n24821","headword_ar":"صَلَاةٌ","root":"Slw","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sal`wp","text_ar":"صَلٰوة"},{"kind":"text","text":", [accord. to El-Hareeree, to be written with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A","text_ar":"ا"},{"kind":"text","text":"when prefixed to a pronoun, and also in the dual number, (see De Sacy's Anthol. Gram. Arabe, p. 67 of the Arabic text,) but this rule I have not found to be generally observed,"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1721},{"kind":"text","text":"even in the best MSS., nor have I in the similar case of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hay`wpN","text_ar":"حَيٰوةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (to which it is also applied,) in the best copies of the Kur-án,] is said to be [originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SalawapN","text_ar":"صَلَوَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEalapN","text_ar":"فَعَلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Mgh, MF, TA,) or, accord. to some, ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SalowapN","text_ar":"صَلْوَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEolapN","text_ar":"فَعْلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (MF, TA:) it is a quasi-inf. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sal~aY","text_ar":"صَلَّى"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]: (S, K:) and [used as a simple subst.] it signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Prayer, supplication,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"petition:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, Msb, K:) this is said to be its primary signification: and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muSal~FY","text_ar":"مُصَلًّى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is said to have the same meaning. (Msb, TA.) ―         -b2-  Then applied to signify"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain well-known mode,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"manner,"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of religious service,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] because comprising prayer; (Msb;) [the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"divinelyappointed act of prayer;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one of the divinelyappointed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SalawaAt","text_ar":"صَلَوَات"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain religious service in which are"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rukuwE","text_ar":"رُكُوع"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lowering of the head so that the palms of the hands reach the knees"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sujuwd","text_ar":"سُجُود"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"prostration of oneself in a particular manner"},{"kind":"text","text":"expl. voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sajada","text_ar":"سَجَدَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (M, * K:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muSal~FY","text_ar":"مُصَلًّى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is said to have the same meaning. (TA.) [The performance of this act is fully described in my work on the Modern Egyptians.] It is said to be, in this sense, a proper term of the law, not indicated by the language of the Arabs [before El-Islám] except as importing prayer, which is its primary signification: what Esh-Shiháb says respecting it necessarily implies its being a proper term of the law known to the Arabs [before ElIslám]: in the Mz it is said to be one of the words of El-Islám: but all of these sayings require consideration. (MF, TA, [Much more, which I omit as being unprofitable, is added on this point in the TA, partly from the Msb; as well as several different opinions respecting the derivation of the word as used in this sense, which are fanciful or absurd.]) The saying of the Prophet,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA Sal`wpa","text_ar":"لَا صَلٰوةَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lijaAri Almasojidi A_il~aA fiY Almasojidi","text_ar":"لِجَارِ المَسْجِدِ اـِلَّا فِى المَسْجِدِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"There is no"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Slwp","text_ar":"صلوة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"divinely-appointed act of prayer"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that is excellent"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"complete"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to the neighbour of the mosque unless in the mosque"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (M.) And his saying, to Usámeh,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlS~al`wpu A^amaAmaka","text_ar":"الصَّلٰوةُ اَمَامَكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The time of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Slwp","text_ar":"صلوة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"divinely-appointed prayer"},{"kind":"text","text":"], or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the place thereof,"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is before thee,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] alluding to that of sunset. (Mgh.) And he used the term"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlS~al`wpu","text_ar":"الصَّلٰوةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suwrapu AlS~al`wpi","text_ar":"سُورَةُ الصَّلٰوةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faAtiHap","text_ar":"فَاتِحَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Opening Chapter of the Kur-án,"},{"kind":"text","text":"because it is a form of prayer, or] because the recital thereof is excellent, or satisfactory. (Mgh.) In the Kur xxii. 41, (I' Ab, S, M, Ksh, Bd,) [the pl.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SalawaAtN","text_ar":"صَلَوَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Places of worship of the Jews:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(I' Ab, S, M, Ksh, Bd, K:) said to be (Ksh, Bd) originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaluwtaA","text_ar":"صَلُوتَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", a Hebrew word, (Ksh, Bd, K,) arabicized: (Ksh, Bd:) this is the common reading of the word, and the most valid: other readings are"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SuluwaAtN","text_ar":"صُلُوَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SulawaAtN","text_ar":"صُلَوَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SilawaAtN","text_ar":"صِلَوَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and beside these, some others which are perverted forms. (TA.) ―         -b3-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Prayer for forgiveness"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pardon."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, Mgh, K.) ―         -b4-  [And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A blessing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an invocation of"},{"kind":"text","text":"God's"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"blessing"},{"kind":"text","text":"upon any one. See 2.] ―         -b5-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"barakapN","text_ar":"بَرَكَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A blessing, such as is bestowed by God"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (Msb:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mercy"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, Mgh, Msb, K) of God (S, M) on his apostle: (M:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"magnification;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and this is [said to be] specially denoted by its verb when the Prophet is the object: (Msb:) and God's"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"eulogy,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"commendation,"},{"kind":"text","text":"bestowed upon his apostle. (M, K.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlS~alaApu","text_ar":"الصَّلَاةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SalFA","text_ar":"صَلًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"] also means"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_itoyaAnu AlmaroA^api fiY","text_ar":"اـِتْيَانُ المَرْاَةِ فِى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"duburihaA","text_ar":"دُبُرِهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Swm","text_ar":"صوم"},{"kind":"text","text":".)"}],"source_refs":["Mgh","MF","TA","S","K","M","Msb","Ksh","Bd"]},{"entry_id":"n24825","headword_ar":"صَلَاهُ","root":"SlY","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, Msb, K,) aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaSoliyhi","text_ar":"يَصْلِيهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaloYN","text_ar":"صَلْىٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He roasted, broiled,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fried, it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"namely, flesh-meat, (S, M, Msb, K,) &c.; (S;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SalaAhu fiY Aln~aAri","text_ar":"صَلَاهُ فِى النَّارِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaY","text_ar":"عَلَى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aln~aAri","text_ar":"النَّارِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signify the same; and also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he burned it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And (so in the M, but in the K “ or ”)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SalaAhu","text_ar":"صَلَاهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY Aln~aAri","text_ar":"فِى النَّارِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He threw it into the fire to be burned;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ASlAhu","text_ar":"اصلاهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sl~Ahu","text_ar":"صلّاهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taSoliyapN","text_ar":"تَصْلِيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA;) namely, flesh-meat. (M, K. [But see the next sentence.]) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SalaAhu Aln~aAra","text_ar":"صَلَاهُ النَّارَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY Aln~aAri","text_ar":"فِى النَّارِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaY Aln~aAri","text_ar":"عَلَى النَّارِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaloYN","text_ar":"صَلْىٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SuliY~N","text_ar":"صُلِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SiliY~N","text_ar":"صِلِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aln~aAra","text_ar":"النَّارَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ASlAhu","text_ar":"اصلاهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aln~aAra","text_ar":"النَّارَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sl~Ahu","text_ar":"صلّاهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":";"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made him to enter into the fire, and to remain, stay, dwell,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abide, therein:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN Aln~aAra","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ النَّارَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sul~iYa","text_ar":"صُلِّىَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such as one was made to enter into the fire,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]: (M:) [or] you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Salayotu","text_ar":"صَلَيْتُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~ajula naArFA","text_ar":"الرَّجُلَ نَارًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I made the man to enter fire and to be burned:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSolayotuhu","text_ar":"اَصْلَيْتُهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A","text_ar":"ا"},{"kind":"text","text":", when you mean"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I threw him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cast him, into the fire, as though intending burning"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"him"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sal~ayotuhu","text_ar":"صَلَّيْتُهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taSoliyapN","text_ar":"تَصْلِيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S.) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Salayotu fulaAnFA","text_ar":"صَلَيْتُ فُلَانًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, TA,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lifulaAnK","text_ar":"لِفُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, TA,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I laboured in a case,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an affair, desiring to calumniate,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"slander, such a one therein, and to cause him to fall into destruction:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, TA:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Salayotuhu","text_ar":"صَلَيْتُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Salayotu lahu","text_ar":"صَلَيْتُ لَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"both signify"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I calumniated,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"slandered, him, and caused him to fall into destruction,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in consequence thereof:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M:) or, accord. to the K,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SalaY","text_ar":"صَلَى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnFA","text_ar":"فُلَانًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", of which the inf. n. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaloYN","text_ar":"صَلْىٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he soothed, coaxed, wheedled,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cajoled, such a one:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"deceived, deluded, beguiled, circumvented,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"outwitted, him:"},{"kind":"text","text":"which meanings are not in any of the three lexicons above mentioned: accord. to the A,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Salayotu bifulaAnK","text_ar":"صَلَيْتُ بِفُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[probably a mistranscription for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lifulaAnK","text_ar":"لِفُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"] means (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I framed a stratagem,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"plot, to cause such a one to fall;"},{"kind":"text","text":"there said to be tropical. (TA.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SalaY yadahu biAln~aAri","text_ar":"صَلَى يَدَهُ بِالنَّارِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[said in the TA to be a mistake]: see 2.       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaliYa Aln~aAra","text_ar":"صَلِىَ النَّارَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, Msb, K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biAln~aAri","text_ar":"بِالنَّارِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, Msb, K,) aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaSolaY","text_ar":"يَصْلَى"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, * K, *) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SalFY","text_ar":"صَلًى"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SuliY~N","text_ar":"صُلِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K, ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaloyFA","text_ar":"صَلْيًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the CK being a mistranscription for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Suliy~FA","text_ar":"صُلِيًّا"},{"kind":"text","text":",]) or both, (M,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SiliY~N","text_ar":"صِلِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SilaA='N","text_ar":"صِلَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,) and accord. to the K"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SalaA='N","text_ar":"صَلَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", but this is a mistake for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SalFY","text_ar":"صَلًى"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, burned"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by the fire"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he endured,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"suffered, the heat of the fire;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aln~aAra","text_ar":"النَّارَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tSl~Y","text_ar":"تصلّى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he felt the heat of the fire:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) and one says ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tSl~Y","text_ar":"تصلّى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Har~a Aln~aAri","text_ar":"حَرَّ النَّارِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ASTlAhu","text_ar":"اصطلاهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in this last sense or in the sense next preceding]: (Ham p. 792:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaliYa","text_ar":"صَلِىَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aln~aAra","text_ar":"النَّارَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he entered into the fire:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"blh","text_ar":"بله"},{"kind":"text","text":": see an ex. voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baloha","text_ar":"بَلْهَ"},{"kind":"text","text":":) or, accord. to Er-Rághib,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaliYa","text_ar":"صَلِىَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biAln~aAri","text_ar":"بِالنَّارِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he was tried"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buliYa","text_ar":"بُلِىَ"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by fire,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by the fire;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and so"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bika*aA","text_ar":"بِكَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by such a thing, as though by fire"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) [In the Kur, in which are many exs. of it, (iv. 11, xiv. 34, xvii. 19, &c.,) it is always trans. by itself, without"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bi","text_ar":"بِ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaliYa biAlA^amori","text_ar":"صَلِىَ بِالاَمْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, *) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biAlHarobi","text_ar":"بِالحَرْبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^amora","text_ar":"الاَمْرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tSl~Y","text_ar":"تصلّى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHaroba","text_ar":"الحَرْبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He endured,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"suffered, the heat,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"severity,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vehemence, of the affair,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"case,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the war,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fight:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M:) Aboo-Zubeyd says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"Har~a Harobihimu ↓ \n      faqado taSal~ayotu\n                      \n                     \n                        Almaqoruwru mino qarasi ↓ \n      kamaA taSal~aY"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And I have suffered the heat and vehemence of their war, like as he who is affected with cold suffers in consequence of coldest and most abundant hoar-frost"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (M.)       -A3-  [It is said that]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaliYa","text_ar":"صَلِىَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~ajulu","text_ar":"الرَّجُلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lazima","text_ar":"لَزِمَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The man kept to,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"clave to,"},{"kind":"text","text":"a thing]; and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ASTlY","text_ar":"اصطلى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": whence Zj holds"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SalaApN","text_ar":"صَلَاةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[expl. in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Slw","text_ar":"صلو"},{"kind":"text","text":"] to be derived; because it is a keeping, or cleaving, to that which God has appointed: and hence also, [it is said,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY Aln~aAri","text_ar":"فِى النَّارِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mano yuSal~aY","text_ar":"مَنْ يُصَلَّى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ylzm","text_ar":"يلزم"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yulozamu","text_ar":"يُلْزَمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mano yulozamu Aln~aAra","text_ar":"مَنْ يُلْزَمُ النَّارَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He who is made to keep,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cleave, to the fire;"},{"kind":"text","text":"nearly agreeing with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sal~aAhu Aln~aAra","text_ar":"صَلَّاهُ النَّارَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as expl. above from the M and K]. (TA.)       -A4-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Salayotu AlZ~ahora","text_ar":"صَلَيْتُ الظَّهْرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I struck,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"beat, that part of the back which is called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SalFA","text_ar":"صَلًا"},{"kind":"text","text":": or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I hit that part:"},{"kind":"text","text":"but this is extr.; for by rule it should be"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Salawotuhu","text_ar":"صَلَوْتُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like as Hudheyl say. (M. [See 1 in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Slw","text_ar":"صلو"},{"kind":"text","text":".])"}],"source_refs":["S","M","Msb","K","T","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}